Package: Rtorch
Type: Package
Title: High-Performance R Bindings to libtorch
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Troy", "Hernandez", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                   email = "troy@cornball.ai")
Description: Direct R bindings to 'libtorch' with minimal overhead. Provides a
    'torch'-compatible API that eliminates intermediate layers ('Rcpp', lantern,
    R7 dispatch) for maximum performance on tensor operations. Includes an
    expression compiler that optimizes R 'torch' code into fused SIMD kernels.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/cornball-ai/Rtorch
BugReports: https://github.com/cornball-ai/Rtorch/issues
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Suggests: tinytest, digest, ariel
VignetteBuilder: simplermarkdown
NeedsCompilation: yes
SystemRequirements: libtorch (reuses installed torch package)
